newsitem.title: DUBAI: Dubai port volume up six pct in first nine months.
newsitem.headline: Dubai port volume up six pct in first nine months.

text.p: Dubai Ports Authority (DPA) said on Sunday total tonnage handled at its Port Rashid and Jebel Ali harbours rose six percent to about 22.4 million tonnes in the first nine months of this year.

The authority said in a statement the increase came mainly from handling 50 percent more asphalt, 30 percent more bulk grains, 26 percent more frozen food, fruit and vegetables, and 16 percent more timber.
Container traffic was also up in the January to September period, with the number of standard container units handled rising nine percent to 1.67 million.
A total of 7,121 vessels called at the DPA's ports in the first nine months of the year, including 2,964 container vessels.
